---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

const lastUpdated = "June 1, 2026";
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy | Fjord Apps"
  description="Privacy policy covering the Fjord Apps mobile applications."
  noindex={true}
>
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-8">
        <img
          src="/images/fjordlabsicon.png"
          alt="Fjord Apps"
          class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full"
        />
        <div>
          <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-heading font-bold text-bark">
            Privacy Policy
          </h1>
          <p class="text-sm text-bark/50">Fjord Apps</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-bark/40 mb-8">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <div class="prose-article">
        <p>
          This privacy policy applies to the mobile applications published by
          Fjord Apps, including <strong>Brewio</strong>,
          <strong>Just Pomodoro</strong>, and <strong>Gissa</strong>
          (collectively, the “Apps”). These Apps share a single account and
          authentication system, so one policy covers all of them.
        </p>

        <p>
          We are committed to keeping your data private. We do not sell, rent,
          or share your personal information with advertisers or third-party
          marketers.
        </p>

        <h2>What We Collect</h2>

        <p>
          We only collect the minimum data needed to provide the Apps and make
          them work across your devices:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Account information.</strong> When you sign in, we store the
            account identifier provided by your chosen sign-in method (email
            address, Apple Sign In, or Google). Authentication is handled
            securely through Supabase.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>App usage data.</strong> We store the content and settings
            you create within an App so it can be saved and synced to your
            account — for example, your entries, preferences, and progress. This
            data is used solely to operate the App for you.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          We do <strong>not</strong> collect data for advertising, profiling, or
          any purpose other than running the Apps you use.
        </p>

        <h2>How We Use Your Data</h2>

        <ul>
          <li>To authenticate you and keep you signed in.</li>
          <li>To save your content and sync it across your devices.</li>
          <li>To provide, maintain, and improve the functionality of the Apps.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Shared Account Across Apps</h2>

        <p>
          The Fjord Apps use a single, shared authentication system. This means
          you can sign in to any of our Apps with one account. Your account
          identity is shared across the Apps, but the content you create in each
          App is associated with your account and used only to operate that
          experience for you.
        </p>

        <h2>Data Storage and Security</h2>

        <p>
          Your data is stored using Supabase, which provides secure,
          industry-standard infrastructure for authentication and database
          storage. Access to your data is protected so that only your account
          can read and write it.
        </p>

        <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>

        <p>
          We rely on a small number of trusted service providers to operate the
          Apps:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Supabase</strong> — authentication and database storage.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Apple and Google</strong> — sign-in providers, if you choose
            to use them.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          These providers process data only as needed to provide their service
          and are bound by their own privacy policies.
        </p>

        <h2>Data Retention and Deletion</h2>

        <p>
          We keep your data for as long as you maintain an account. You can
          delete your account and associated data at any time from within the
          App. Once deleted, your data is removed from our systems.
        </p>

        <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>

        <p>
          The Apps are not directed at children under the age of 13, and we do
          not knowingly collect personal information from children.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>

        <p>
          We may update this privacy policy from time to time. When we do, we
          will revise the “Last updated” date at the top of this page.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
